<p>Let‚Äôs look at another example that will help us intuitively understand this idea. We know in Model 1 that \(\begin{bmatrix} 0.5 \\ 2 \end{bmatrix}\) labels <img src="/cob/cat.PNG" width="50" height="40" />. But just like before, \(\color{#CBC3E3}{\begin{bmatrix} 0.5 \\ 2 \end{bmatrix}}\) in Model 2 does not.</p>

